168. Excel Sheet Column Title

Given a positive integer, return its corresponding column title as appear in an Excel sheet.	

  1 -> A
    2 -> B
    3 -> C
	
	Input: 701
Output: "ZY"

class Solution {
public:
    string convertToTitle(int n) {
        string result="";
        while(n)
        {
            result +=(--n) % 26 + 'A';
            n /=26;
        }
        reverse(result.begin(),result.end());
        return result;
    }
};

/* Let's consider a tough example 701 whose answer is ZY
We know A-Z is 26 letters and we have to break them accordingly, so take number
decrease the number by 1 take mod and add A example 701-1 = 700 % 26 = 24 + 'A' = 'Y', 700/26=26 and repeat you get 'z', then reverse it to get the result. The first loop works with O(n/26).
*/